article.headline: Northern Iowa 86, Wagner 56
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa (AP) -- Ben Jacobson led four Northern Iowa players in double figures with 15 points and the Panthers shot 59 percent in beating Wagner 86-56 Tuesday night. Eric Coleman and Erik Crawford added 13 points apiece and Grant Stout had 12 for Northern Iowa (6-2), which won for the fifth time in six games. The only loss in that stretch was at No. 17 Iowa, 76-73. Northern Iowa scored the game's first eight points, opened a 15-1 lead after less than 5 1/2 minutes and Wagner (1-7) never recovered, trailing by as many as 27 in the first half. Matt Vitale made four 3-pointers and led Wagner with 19 points, while Mark Porter scored 13. Porter was the only Wagner starter who could score with any consistency. The four others combined for just 17 points on 7-for-23 shooting. It was the second of three games in Iowa for the Seahawks, who lost to Iowa State 62-50 on Sunday and play at Drake on Thursday. Northern Iowa coach Greg McDermott used 13 players and all but starting point guard Brooks McKowen scored, McKowen contributed six assists and a steal. Crawford hit two 3-pointers and Stout one to spark Northern Iowa's early burst. The Panthers led 35-9 after Coleman scored with 4:49 left in the first half and Wagner did not reach double figures until James Ulrich hit a jumper at the 3:04 mark. Wagner shot only 28.6 percent (8-for-28) in the first half and was never closer than 15 in the second half. The Panthers then steadily increased their lead and were up 83-49 with less than two minutes to play.
